{"contentApi":{"id":"world/2012/dec/15/mary-sherlach-psychologist-sandy-hook","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news","webPublicationDate":1355585040000,"webTitle":"Mary Sherlach: Sandy Hook psychologist preparing for retirement","webUrl":"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/dec/15/mary-sherlach-psychologist-sandy-hook","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/world/2012/dec/15/mary-sherlach-psychologist-sandy-hook","fields":{"trailText":"<p>Sherlach had worked at Sandy Hook elementary school for 18 years and was familiar face, giving students help and support</p>","headline":"Mary Sherlach: Sandy Hook school psychologist preparing for retirement","body":"<p>One of the six adults to have died in the Newtown school shooting was a long-serving member of staff, familiar to students and parents.</p><p>Mary Sherlach, the 56-year-old school psychologist, had worked at the Sandy Hook elementary school for 18 years, giving support and guidance to the young children.</p><p>Sherlach's website gives evidence of a life dedicated to her profession. A master's and a sixth year professional degree from Southern Connecticut State University followed an undergraduate degree in psychology from SUNY Cortland.</p><p>Before starting at Sandy Hook in 1994, she worked in three other school districts.</p><p>&quot;She wanted to help kids get over their problems and go on to be successful,&quot; her son-in-law Eric Schwartz <a href=\"http://newtown.patch.com/articles/mary-sherlach-ct-school-shooting-victim-looked-ahead-to-next-stage-of-life-936a195c\">told the Newtown Patch</a>.</p><p>A freelance writer for the newspaper, Schwartz said that the family were in shock.</p><p>&quot;I still don't think anyone's fully grasped it. It doesn't feel real. It's hard to wrap your head around it,&quot; the Patch reported.</p><p><a href=\"http://myschooldesk.net/newtown/teachersite.aspx#site.7325_pid.31151_mid.56275\">Sherlach's website</a> also gives testimony of a happy life outside work.</p><p>Married for 31 years to husband Bill, the pair have two daughters aged 25 and 28. The New York Times reported that the couple lived in Trumbull, Connecticut.</p><p>John Button, 57, a friend of Sherlach's husband, <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/15/nyregion/sandy-hook-principal-and-school-psychologist-went-the-extra-mile.html?hp&amp;_r=0\">told the New York Times</a> that she was preparing for retirement. &quot;It was going to be her last year — that's what she said,&quot; he said. &quot;She loved her job. She's done this for her whole career.&quot;</p><p>When not at work, the couple enjoyed &quot;spending time at our lake house in the Finger Lakes,&quot; Sherlach wrote on her website, adding: &quot;My hobbies include gardening, reading and the theater.&quot;</p><p>But the overarching image that emerges is of a woman who loved her work. She wrote: &quot;I truly enjoy working with the SHS (Sandy Hook School) staff, parents and children and am always ready to assist in problem solving, intervention and prevention.&quot;</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/401131890|2012-12-22T11:49:05Z|6bf9c8556cae36743fd222f0fd2c2cd3d76709f7 -->","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2012-12-16T04:46:34Z","hasStoryPackage":"true","score":"1.0","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2012/12/15/1355609849742/Dawn-Sherlach-with-her-hu-005.jpg","standfirst":"Sherlach had worked at Sandy Hook elementary school for 18 years and was familiar face, giving students help and support","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3ch7c","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2012/12/15/1355609849742/Dawn-Sherlach-with-her-hu-005.jpg","wordcount":"302","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"401131890","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Matt Williams","publication":"guardian.co.uk","internalPageCode":"1843113","shouldHideAdverts":"false","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2012-12-18T1